Tallahassee.David S. Walker Library: The David S. Walker Library (also known as The University Library) is a historic library in Tallahassee, Florida named for Governor David S. Walker, who served from 1865 through 1868. For many years it housed Tallahassee's public library.It is located 209 East Park Avenue. On June 22, 1976, it was added to the U.S. National Register of Historic Places.
